{
  "stem": "1858.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 310.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And whenever she saw the Nazi guard approaching, she would help her to get up on her feet, lean on the machine so she could at least pretend she is working.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were angry at the nurse, who was a girl, one of us, from our hometown, whom we knew.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why would she do that?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But when we returned that day from the factory, we knew why.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She either heard something, overheard something, knew something.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's why she pushed those that could barely stand on their feet out of the sick room.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For that day, while we were at work, the Gestapo came, took all the sick girls from the sick room, shipped them out of our camp, and we never saw them again.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So by doing what she did, she saved the lives of the few girls that she helped, and she made them go to work that day.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we first were so angry at her, not knowing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My sister survived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't realize then that she sacrificed her life, that girl.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because had the Nazis known what she did, she would too have been taken away.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So there were all kinds of acts of heroism in a way.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was heroic.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But trying just to live and survive, I think, is the greatest act of heroism under the condition that we lived.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Wanting to live, wanting to survive, is, I think, heroism.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because it would have been so easy to give up, and to die, and to perish, and to stop suffering so much, yet, I, for example, never gave up.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And most of us never.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because, as I said, once you give up, there was nothing to sustain you and you perished.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
